Class User

java.lang.Object
User
All Implemented Interfaces:
IPasswordUpdate
Direct Known Subclasses:
Admin, Doctor, Patient, Pharmacist
public class User extends Object implements IPasswordUpdate
The `User` class represents a user in the system with attributes such as user ID, name, role, gender, and contact information. It also manages password-related operations, including first login password reset and updating the password in the corresponding CSV file.

    • User

      public User(String userID, String name, String password, UserRole role, String gender, String contactEmail, String contactNumber)
      Constructs a `User` object with the specified attributes. A new user is initialized with a default password.
      Parameters:
      userID - The unique identifier for the user.
      name - The name of the user.
      password - The user's password (initially set to a default value).
      role - The role of the user (e.g., Patient, Doctor, Admin).
      gender - The gender of the user.
      contactEmail - The user's contact email.
      contactNumber - The user's contact number.

    • authenticatePassword

      public boolean authenticatePassword(String password)
      Authenticates the user using the provided password. If the provided password matches the current password and the current password is the default password, the user is prompted to reset their password.
      Parameters:
      passString - The password to authenticate.
      Returns:
      `true` if authentication is successful, `false` otherwise.
